</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="86" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1082,1683]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,1190,1215]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dorsal keel on pereonites 
<number box="[640,682,1190,1214]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="4.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="1.0">1–7</number>
very shallow. Antenna 
<number box="[964,978,1190,1214]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="1.0">1</number>
peduncular article 
<number box="[1207,1221,1190,1214]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="2.0">2</number>
longer than wide. Coxae 
<number box="[234,276,1226,1250]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
with very few short setae on the distal margins of. Pereopods 
<number box="[1002,1044,1226,1250]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="4.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="1.0">1–7</number>
propodi without additional robust setae half-way on posterior and anterior margins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="86" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1082,1683]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,1299,1323]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hirayama" box="[323,519,1298,1322]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" refString="Hirayama, A. (1987) Taxonomic studies on the shallow water gammaridean Amphipoda of West Kyushu, Japan. VII. Melitidae (Melita), Melphidippidae, Oedicerotidae, Phliantidae and Phoxocephalidae. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 32, 1 - 62." type="journal article" year="1987">
Hirayama (
<number box="[452,511,1298,1322]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="1987.0">1987</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
originally called this species 
<taxonomicName box="[868,1222,1299,1323]" class="Malacostraca" family="Phliantidae" genus="Palinnotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thomsoni" subSpecies="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[868,1222,1299,1323]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="86">Palinnotus thomsoni japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not knowing that 
<bibRefCitation author="Tzvetkova" box="[153,356,1334,1358]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" refString="Tzvetkova, N. L. (1967) On the fauna and ecology of amphipods (Amphipoda, Gammaridea) of Possjet Bay, (Sea of Japan). Akademija Nauk SSSR, Zoologicheskii Institut, Issledovanija Fauny Morei, 5, 160 - 195, 7 figs., [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="1967">
Tzvetkova (
<number box="[289,347,1334,1358]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="1967.0">1967</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
had already used the name and thus creating a junior homonym. We raise the subspecies to species status, and at the same time, give it the new name, 
<taxonomicName box="[810,1066,1371,1395]" class="Malacostraca" family="Phliantidae" genus="Pereionotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirayamai">
<emphasis box="[810,1066,1371,1395]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="86">Pereionotus hirayamai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1082,1683]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86">
<bibRefCitation author="Coleman" box="[197,394,1406,1430]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" refString="Coleman, C. O. (2009 b) Phliantidae. In: Lowry, J. K. &amp; Myers, A. A. (Eds) (2009) Benthic Amphipoda (Crustacea: Peracarida) of the Great Barrier Reef, Australia. Zootaxa, 2260, 766 - 770." type="journal article" year="2009" yearSuffix="b">
Coleman (
<number box="[313,372,1406,1430]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="2009.0">2009</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that 
<taxonomicName box="[582,740,1407,1431]" class="Malacostraca" family="Phliantidae" genus="Palinnotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thomsoni" subSpecies="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[582,740,1407,1431]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="86">P. t. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was probably an undescribed species due to many differences to the Australian material.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1082,1683]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86">
<bibRefCitation author="Hirayama" box="[197,389,1478,1502]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" refString="Hirayama, A. (1987) Taxonomic studies on the shallow water gammaridean Amphipoda of West Kyushu, Japan. VII. Melitidae (Melita), Melphidippidae, Oedicerotidae, Phliantidae and Phoxocephalidae. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 32, 1 - 62." type="journal article" year="1987">
Hirayama (
<number box="[323,381,1478,1502]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="1987.0">1987</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered that compared with 
<emphasis box="[749,875,1478,1503]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="86">P. t h o m s o n i</emphasis>
: the propodus of gnathopod 
<number box="[1203,1217,1478,1502]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="1.0">1</number>
is less setose; coxa 
<number box="[153,167,1514,1538]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="4.0">4</number>
is prominently extended posteromedially; the peduncle of uropod 
<number box="[914,928,1514,1538]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="2.0">2</number>
is lacking the inner triangular expansion; the inner plate of maxilla 
<number box="[406,420,1550,1574]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="1.0">1</number>
is prominently smaller; the distal protrusion of peduncular article 
<number box="[1179,1193,1550,1574]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="1.0">1</number>
of antenna 
<number box="[1329,1343,1550,1574]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="1.0">1</number>
is more pronounced; and the protrusions on the head, pereon and pleon are more developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1082,1683]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86">
Unlike 
<bibRefCitation author="Hirayama" box="[282,475,1622,1646]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" refString="Hirayama, A. (1987) Taxonomic studies on the shallow water gammaridean Amphipoda of West Kyushu, Japan. VII. Melitidae (Melita), Melphidippidae, Oedicerotidae, Phliantidae and Phoxocephalidae. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 32, 1 - 62." type="journal article" year="1987">
Hirayama (
<number box="[409,467,1622,1646]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="1987.0">1987</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
we consider these to be species level differences. Because 
<taxonomicName authority="Tzvetkova, 1967" authorityName="Tzvetkova" authorityYear="1967" class="Malacostraca" family="Phliantidae" genus="Pereionotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[1155,1293,1623,1647]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="86">P. japonicus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tzvetkova" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" refString="Tzvetkova, N. L. (1967) On the fauna and ecology of amphipods (Amphipoda, Gammaridea) of Possjet Bay, (Sea of Japan). Akademija Nauk SSSR, Zoologicheskii Institut, Issledovanija Fauny Morei, 5, 160 - 195, 7 figs., [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="1967">
Tzvetkova, 
<number box="[153,210,1658,1682]" pageId="23" pageNumber="86" value="1967.0">1967</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is already in use, we are giving this species the name 
<emphasis box="[824,963,1659,1683]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="86">P. h ir a y a m a i</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
